The '''grey-hooded heleia''' ('''''Heleia pinaiae'''''), also known as the '''grey-hooded white-eye'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldbirdnames.org/new/ioc-lists/master-list-2/ |title=Master Lists: v15.1 |website=[[IOC World Bird List]] |publisher=[[International Ornithologists' Union]] |access-date=13 March 2025}}</ref> and '''grey-hooded ibon''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Zosteropidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Seram Island]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]].

